   Bison Futé sur tous vos trajets, du départ à l'arrivée
   ombre
   Traffic information related to road safety - Action c -

   The Commission delegated Regulation (EU) n° 886/2013 of 15 May 2013 -
   called Regulation action "c" - is supplementing Directive 201/40/EU -
   called Directive ITS. This delegated Regulation precises data and
   procedures for the provision, where possible, of road safety-related
   minimum universal traffic information free of charge to users.

   The list of road safety-related events or conditions covered consists
   of the 7 following categories, choosen by France :
     * 1° temporary slippery road ;
     * 2° animal, people, obstacles, debris on the road ;
     * 3° unprotected accident area ;
     * 4° short-term road works ;
     * 5° reduced visibility ;
     * 6° wrong-way driver ;
     * 7° unmanaged blockage of a road.

   The geographical scope of collect and broadcast for road operators is
   the national road network.

   This page represents the French national access point for datas action
   « c ».

References :

   Directive 2010/40/UE of the European Parliament and of the Council
   (Format pdf - 785.6 kb - 20/03/2018) of 7 July 2010 on the framework
   for the deployment of Intelligent Transport Systems in the field of
   road transport and for interfaces with other modes of transport.

   Commission delegated Regulation (EU) n° 886/2013 (Format pdf - 737.6 kb
   - 30/03/2018) of 15 May 2013 with regard to data and procedures for the
   provision, where possible, of road safety-related minimum universal
   traffic information free of charge to users.

   Decree n° 2015-474 (Format pdf - 143.9 kb - 19/10/2018) of 27 April
   2015 with regard to the provision of information services for safe and
   secure parking places for trucks and commercial vehicles and data and
   procedures road-safety related traffic information.

   Order of 27 April 2015 (Format pdf - 141.3 kb - 19/10/2018) with regard
   to data and procedures for the provision of road safety-related traffic
   information.
   Ministère de la transition écologique et solidaire

